From 4e350df87f7ad9e19393ba111c130f191bcf6639 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: KITOHSY <hongsun900912@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 10:00:14 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 02/11] T13: add moonlight:// URL handler and single-instance
 forwarding
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SmartClassroom T13 — moonlight-qt fork. Wires the `moonlight://connect?...`
URL produced by the SmartClassroom frontend into the new `connect` CLI
subcommand:

  * scT13ExpandMoonlightConnectUrl() rewrites any moonlight:// URL inside
    argv into the equivalent `connect <host> --port <port> --connect-token
    <token> --host-id <id>` shape that the standard CLI parser already
    understands, so URL launches and direct CLI invocations share a single
    dispatch path.
  * QDesktopServices::setUrlHandler("moonlight", ...) registers a macOS
    QFileOpenEvent-driven handler so URLs delivered after the event loop
    starts also land in the same path.
  * QLocalServer/QLocalSocket give us single-instance behaviour for URL
    clicks. A second-instance process that sees a moonlight:// URL in its
    own argv forwards them to the running first instance and exits with
    status 0; the first instance routes received URLs through
    QDesktopServices::openUrl so they re-enter the local handler.
  * A new ConnectRequested switch arm lands the user on PcView and logs
    the parsed connect parameters. The receiver-side dispatch into
    ComputerManager (host auto-add + pending-token storage) is added in
    the next patch in this series; keeping it as a logging stub here lets
    the URL plumbing be reviewed and built independently.

CLI-only re-entry forwarding (e.g. `moonlight connect ...` typed while
another Moonlight is already running) is intentionally out of scope for
T13 v1 — the KPI path is the URL form. A v1.1 follow-up can extend the
receiver to re-parse forwarded non-URL argv if that becomes a real user
flow.
